        <p n="1-2">
      			Ninth year of the victorious king Para<supplied reason="undefined">me</supplied>śvaravarmaṉ.
      		</p>
        <p n="3-8">
      			Mukaṉ<!--Update:add markup for translation unclear, tentative-->, the son <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Pāratāyar, the lord of Mēṟceṅkai<note>Alternatively, simply "Pāratāyar of Mēṟceṅkai".</note><!--Update: translate: māmm. Part of the placename-->, fell recovering cattle, when <supplied reason="undefined">Va</supplied>miṟaiyār<!--Update:add markup for translation unclear, tentative-->, a temple dignitary <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>kōyil paṭṭar</foreign>
          </supplied> in Iḷakkōvūrnāṭu in Vēṇāṭu, came and seized cattle.

